23/10/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- Police announced on Thursday (October 22nd) they busted a drug trafficking gang in Athens, seizing 135kg of heroin. Nine foreign nationals have been arrested -- six Syrians, one Bangladeshi, a Sudanese and a Romanian woman, who allegedly smuggled the drugs from Turkey. All nine have been charged. The operation was conducted after a two-month investigation, which uncovered a drug lab operating under the guise of a clothing shop. (ANA-MPA, BTA - 22/10/09) 
